      <fr:mainmatter>
        <html:p>Aspiring physics student. I recieved my BSc Honours Physics-Chemistry from the <fr:link href="https://www.umanitoba.ca/" type="external">University of Manitoba</fr:link> in 2024. I've worked 2 km underground with the <fr:link href="https://www.picoexperiment.com/" type="external">PICO Collaboration</fr:link> at <fr:link href="https://www.snolab.ca/" type="external">SNOLAB</fr:link>. My research interests are in particle theory, currently focusing in dark matter candidates and in fundamental interactions.</html:p>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
    <html:p>This site is a collection of my scientific notes created using <fr:link href="https://www.forester-notes.org/" type="external">Forester</fr:link>.</html:p>
    <html:p>The general principle is that I keep my notes as atomized concepts (up to the point that I deem is beneficial). I use links between notes to allow an emergent structure rather than imposing a hierchy on the ideas. I later transclude my notes into notebook overviews of the topic in order to conveniently see what I've covered.</html:p>
    <html:p>To navigate my forest press <html:code>Ctrl+K</html:code> and search, or use links between notes. Some notebooks I've made are available <fr:link href="/forest/overview/" title="Overview of Notebooks" uri="https://andrewczezowski.github.io/forest/overview/" display-uri="overview" type="local">here</fr:link>.</html:p>
